			<div class="content" id="post-content-1938598">
									

<p>Thanks, everyone, for the praise and feedback. As my first tale (only two skips before this) I'm delighted by the positive reception.</p>
<p>To be honest, even in my mind, this scenario <strong>isn't</strong> par for the course as to how Directorate K <em>normally</em> operates. I don't have a 100% head-canon for it, yet, but I imagine that many members, including almost all the γ-class, are either memeticaly influenced, possibly from birth, or are subtly contacted at a younger age than this. I imagine the γ-class being guys in yellow ponchos, the sign-cleaners, the quarter-spinner, etc.</p>
<p>Steve Howitt here is either β-class or α-class, and Jack is being recruited to fill a low-level opening in one of those classes as well.</p>
<p>Also, this is probably one of their more overt operations. I imagine that <em>most</em> of the butterfly-effect influences by Directorate-K are much subtler than what's outlined in this story. But I needed to keep it somewhat short, and I needed the reader to be able to follow it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
