			<div class="content" id="post-content-1938677">
									

<p>I have mixed feelings about this, but overall I liked it.</p>
<p>For starters, I knew it had to be a Directorate K tale as soon as it mentioned the bum keeping track of spinning quarters. This pleased me.</p>
<p>The dialogue after the two emails starts getting a little wonky, though. I was actually going to suggest cutting everything after &quot;You have to be shitting me&quot;, to just leave this on a punchline, but then you'd lose the fun explanation of everything that's been going on. I like the idea that the Directorate's activities, at least on the individual level, actually make sense. There's nothing anomalous about what any of those people did; the anomaly is, again, the organization itself, that all this sort of thing can be kept track of and directed.</p>
<p>So like I said, I think you've hit on something really great here. Good work!</p>

