					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=732274&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225575" alt="thedeadlymoose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=732274)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;" >thedeadlymoose</a></span> <span class="odate time_1401938953 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Jun 2014 03:29</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2045901">
									

<p>I'd missed this. You're actually wrong about the dialogue rules. :/ You made a bunch of grammar errors that are just <em>errors</em>, not just personal choices for effect. :P It's true that you can bend a lot of rules to get voice, with dialogue in particular (&quot;What. The. Fuck.&quot; is perfectly fine in dialogue, for example &#8212; or internal monologue for that matter), but stuff like <em>the very second sentence</em> or &quot;&quot;Holy fuuuuuuuuck.&quot; Jack said, shaking his head. &quot; [randomly picked out] are just errors, not acceptable variation. The vast majority of the errors are just errors, unfortunately.</p>
<p>Know the rules before you break 'em!</p>

							</div>

								
